frameDefinitions: This frame describes either the creation of a Flame by a Kindler or non-sentient Cause, or the igniting of Flammables by a Kindler or a Cause.
A Perpetrator (generally intentionally) commits a Crime, i.e. does something not permitted by the laws of society.
An Event takes place at a Place and Time.
In this frame the Patient, an inorganic item, undergoes a chemical process which renders it less useful, desirable or stable. '' '
A Fire burns Fuel, resulting in damage and possibly complete destruction of the Fuel.
A Fuel, some flammable object or substance, ends up on fire.
frameExamples: Taliban militants recently <t>set fire</t> to several schools.
They <t>perpetrated</t> a felony by substituting a lie for negotiations.
Big earthquakes only <t>happen</t> along plate boundaries. INI
A fire that started on Saturday afternoon, the High Glade Fire - located on the Mendocino National Forest's Upper Lake Ranger District - continued to <t>burn</t> actively on Sunday.
